The paper deals with the problem of approximating frequency moments in data streams, which is a classic problem in data structures and algorithms. The techniques used in the paper involve sampling and sketching, which are common tools in the analysis of data streams. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). However, the paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the analysis of the sampling method, as well as computational complexity (cs.CC) in the analysis of the space complexity. The problem of approximating frequency moments is also related to data mining (cs.DM) and signal processing (cs.SI), which are other possible sub-categories.
